<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>push someone’s buttons • push the panic button</xh5><p> <i>push someone’s buttons</i>—(also: press someone’s buttons) draw a strong emotional reaction, especially anger, from a person: He knew how to <u>push my buttons</u> better than anyone else but I kept my cool.</p><p> <i>push the panic button</i>—(also: press the panic button) overreact to a stressful situation: Everybody is concerned but I don’t think anybody ought to <u>push the panic button</u> just yet.</p> </entry>
